These and other objects of the subject invention will become more fully apparent as the following description is read in light of the attached drawings wherein:


FIG. 1 shows a system configuration of a mobile communication system in accordance with a first example of the invention;


FIG. 2 is a block diagram showing an example of an internal configuration of a base station control device connected with radio base stations;


FIG. 3 is a block diagram showing an example of an internal configuration of a radio base station;


FIG. 4 is a flowchart showing procedures that the base station control device performs;


FIG. 5A shows an example of a frame format for error information;


FIG. 5B shows an example of a frame format for receiving data;


FIG. 6 is a block diagram showing an essential part of a data decoding block of a radio base station in accordance with a second example of the invention;


FIG. 7 shows a system configuration of a mobile communication system in accordance with a third example of the invention;


FIG. 8 shows an example of a system configuration of a mobile communication system that is established in accordance with the conventional site diversity receiving method; and


FIG. 9 shows an example of a frame format of information which is transmitted from a radio base station to a base station control device in accordance with the conventional method.

Error frequency of the radio base station 120-1 is "50";


Error frequency of the radio base station 120-2 is "100"; and


Error frequency of the radio base station 120-3 is "200".
